details.text: The United States of America (U.S.A. or USA), commonly known as the United States (U.S. or US) or America, is a country primarily located in North America.

details.name: ISSN (identifier)
details.text: An International Standard Serial Number (ISSN) is an eight-digit serial number used to uniquely identify a serial publication, such as a magazine.

details.name: ISBN (identifier)
details.text: The International Standard Book Number (ISBN) is a numeric commercial book identifier that is intended to be unique.

details.name: Elizabeth II
details.text: Elizabeth II (Elizabeth Alexandra Mary; born 21 April 1926) is Queen of the United Kingdom and 14 other Commonwealth realms.Elizabeth was born in Mayfair, London, as the first child of the Duke and Duchess of York (later King George VI and Queen Elizabeth).

details.name: VIAF (identifier)
details.text: The Virtual International Authority File (VIAF) is an international authority file.

details.name: Help:IPA/English
details.text: Throughout Wikipedia, the pronunciation of words is indicated by means of the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA).

details.name: Help:Authority control
details.text: Authority control is a way of associating a unique identifier to articles on Wikipedia.

details.name: Digital object identifier
details.text: A digital object identifier (DOI) is a persistent identifier or handle used to uniquely identify various objects, standardized by the International Organization for Standardization (ISO).

details.name: Wayback Machine
details.text: The Wayback Machine is a digital archive of the World Wide Web founded by the Internet Archive, a nonprofit based in San Francisco, California.
